{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"17ffd931-754d-47ae-8ec1-b5cec097f718","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the VSTest compatibility layer is disabled by default.** The SDK now exclusively targets Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the newer runner), so `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run the tests.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 – Re-enable VSTest compatibility\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nAnd more importantly, set:\n\n```xml\n<EnableVSTestAdapter>true</EnableVSTestAdapter>\n```\n\nThis brings back the VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` works again.\n\n### Option 2 – Migrate your CI to the new runner (recommended)\nReplace `vstest.console` with `dotnet test` (which in SDK 4.x delegates to Microsoft.Testing.Platform) or invoke the test executable directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n# or\n./TestProject --report-trx\n```\n\nThis is the intended path forward — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the replacement for VSTest.\n\n**TL;DR:** MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter by default. Either set `<EnableVSTestAdapter>true</EnableVSTestAdapter>` or switch your CI from `vstest.console` to `dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9ef1ea49-22c4-47db-a0cc-35717a57e7d9","outputTokens":376,"requestId":"5C25:12F3AB:4B40C6:5E8406:69F565D2"},"id":"0e1a0d4d-d28e-4504-a73b-a85002777ad4","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:47:55.769Z","parentId":"2c67f3b3-de56-404a-986d-8e69deac42df"}
